performance_ratings.collaboration: I believe the best architectural solutions emerge from truly collaborative efforts. My approach is to facilitate and support the team, ensuring everyone—from our visionary designers to our technical staff and external partners—has a voice and feels empowered to contribute. In the China market, I see my role as a bridge, helping to synthesize diverse ideas and cultural nuances into a cohesive project direction. I am grateful for the talented teams I work with and focus on creating an environment of mutual trust and shared purpose.
performance_ratings.professionalism: I endeavor to uphold the highest standards of professionalism that reflect well on Ennead's reputation. This means taking full accountability for my responsibilities, meeting commitments reliably, and always acting with integrity. I try to maintain a calm and constructive demeanor, especially during challenging phases of a project, focusing on solutions rather than problems. I view professionalism as an ongoing practice and consistently look for ways to better represent our firm's values to our clients and partners.

performance_comments.technical_knowledge_expertise_comments: My technical knowledge is built on a strong foundation in architectural design principles, project delivery methodologies, and business development strategies specific to the built environment. I strive to continuously learn from our technical teams and consultants to ensure our proposals and project plans are not only creative but also technically sound and feasible for the China market. This is particularly important when new market opportunities emerge, such as a shift towards sustainable design or a new building typology we will do in China, i.e. Healthcare and Institutional Laboratory.
performance_comments.workflow_implementation_management_execu: I focus on creating and managing efficient workflows to see projects and strategic initiatives through from conception to completion. This involves coordinating closely with our design, marketing, and finance teams to develop winning proposals, and then managing the project lifecycle to deliver on those promises. I rely on our established firm-wide systems and actively seek to improve local implementation, ensuring our operations in China are seamless, integrated, and effective in supporting our creative and business goals.

additional_evaluation_data.additional_resources: We have three offices now. By implementing structured channels for knowledge exchange and strategic alignment, we can better leverage our collective intelligence. This will allow each market to actively learn from the others' experiences, provide cross-regional support, and efficiently share resources, ultimately strengthening our firm's global position and driving unified growth.
